ğŸ”¹ Project Overview

Minimal Blog is a modern blogging application where users can:

âœï¸ Create, read, update, and delete posts (CRUD)

ğŸ–¼ View posts in a responsive card-based grid

ğŸ“ Edit posts inline with pre-filled form data

ğŸ—‘ Delete posts with confirmation and feedback

It uses Server-Side Rendering (SSR) with Next.js and RESTful APIs built in Node.js with Express, connecting to MongoDB for persistent storage.

ğŸ’» Technologies Used

Frontend:

Next.js 13+ (App Router)

React 18+ (Functional components + hooks)

TypeScript

Tailwind CSS (Responsive + Dark Mode + Modern UI)

Backend:

Node.js + Express

MongoDB + Mongoose

dotenv for environment variables

REST APIs (CRUD for posts)

Other Tools:

VSCode / WebStorm

Postman / Insomnia for API testing

Git for version control

ğŸš€ Features

âœ… Full CRUD functionality

âœ… Dynamic routing for editing posts (/edit/[id])

âœ… Responsive design (mobile, tablet, desktop)

âœ… Dark mode support

âœ… Skeleton loading & error handling

âœ… Optimized fetch logic with useCallback

âœ… TypeScript interfaces for type safety

âœ… Confirmation modal for deletion

âœ… SEO-friendly pages with SSR

ğŸ—„ Backend Details

Folder: /backend
Server: Node.js + Express

Method	Route	Description
GET	/api/posts	Get all posts
GET	/api/posts/:id	Get a post by ID
POST	/api/posts	Create a new post
PUT	/api/posts/:id	Update a post by ID
DELETE	/api/posts/:id	Delete a post by ID

Database Schema (Mongoose):

interface Post {
  title: string;
  content: string;
  author?: string;
  createdAt?: Date;
}

